This project is a browser port of the Plapre Danish text-to-speech system. It is
"Adapted Material" in the sense of CC BY 4.0: it incorporates, reimplements, or
derives from the works below. If you redistribute this project or artifacts
produced from it (including the converted ONNX models), you must preserve this
attribution.

================================================================================
Primary upstream work
================================================================================

Plapre (Danish TTS model + reference pipeline)
  syv.ai — https://syv.ai/produkter/plapre
  Model:  https://huggingface.co/syvai/plapre-pico
  Code:   https://github.com/syv-ai/plapre
  License: CC BY 4.0
  Role: This repository converts the Plapre model (language model, speaker
        projection, built-in speaker embeddings) to ONNX and reimplements its
        inference pipeline (tokenization, normalization, autoregressive sampling)
        in TypeScript. The Plapre weights themselves are license-gated on
        Hugging Face and are NOT redistributed here.

================================================================================
Models and components incorporated by Plapre / this port
================================================================================

Kanade speech tokenizer (neural audio codec: decoder + clone encoder)
  frothywater — https://github.com/frothywater/kanade-tokenizer
  Model:  https://huggingface.co/frothywater/kanade-25hz-clean
  License: MIT (see the MIT notice below)
  Role: Source of the Kanade decoder and the speaker (clone) encoder converted to
        ONNX in conversion/ and redistributed at
        https://huggingface.co/elgehelge/plapre-onnx-web.

HiFT vocoder
  Originating from CosyVoice 2 (FunAudioLLM / Alibaba)
  https://github.com/FunAudioLLM/CosyVoice — License: Apache-2.0
  Role: mel-spectrogram to 24 kHz waveform. Reimplemented with a real-valued
        (i)STFT for ONNX export in conversion/hift_onnx.py. Per the Apache-2.0
        license, attribution is retained in this NOTICE.

WavLM (speech SSL frontend used by the Kanade clone encoder)
  Microsoft — https://github.com/microsoft/unilm/tree/master/wavlm
  License: MIT (see the MIT notice below)
  Role: Frontend of the voice-cloning speaker encoder.

SmolLM2-135M (base architecture of the Plapre language model)
  Hugging Face — https://huggingface.co/HuggingFaceTB/SmolLM2-135M
  License: Apache-2.0

================================================================================
Bundled / runtime third-party software (web library)
================================================================================

onnxruntime-web — Microsoft — License: MIT
  In-browser ONNX inference (WebGPU + WASM).

@huggingface/transformers — Hugging Face — License: Apache-2.0
  Used for the BPE tokenizer (PreTrainedTokenizer).

@breezystack/lamejs — License: LGPL-3.0
  Pure-JS MP3 encoder used by the OpenAI/ElevenLabs format adapters. LGPL-3.0
  obligations apply to this component when redistributed; it is consumed as an
  unmodified dependency.

================================================================================
Build-time only (not redistributed in the published package)
================================================================================

num2words — License: LGPL-2.1
  Used in conversion/ to generate the Danish number-to-words golden fixture that
  the TypeScript reimplementation is tested against. Not shipped at runtime.

PyTorch, Transformers, ONNX, optimum, and related Python packages are used only
by the conversion toolchain (conversion/) to export models; see
conversion/pyproject.toml for the full set and their respective licenses.

